-- Oxford Beats Cambridge 21-10 at Twickenham in Rugby's 129th Varsity Match
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-12-09T16:31:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-09/oxford-beats-cambridge-21-10-at-twickenham-in-rugby-s-129th-varsity-match.html
Oxford University defeated Cambridge
University 21-10 in rugby union’s 129th  Varsity Match .  Oxford  outscored Cambridge two tries to one at Twickenham
Stadium in London. Alex Cheesman and James Crozier touched down
for the Dark Blues and Charlie Marr kicked 11 points.  Jimmy Richards kicked five points for  Cambridge , which also
got a penalty try. The Light Blues hold a 61 to 54 lead in the
series with 14 ties.  Marr opened the scoring with a penalty in the 21st minute,
then converted Cheesman’s try one minute later. Crozier touched
down six minutes later to give Oxford a 15-0 lead.  Cambridge captain Richards then missed a penalty attempt,
before making one just before halftime to make the score 15-3.  Cambridge’s Rob Stevens had a try disallowed in the 54th
minute because of a forward pass. The Light Blues were then
awarded a penalty try, with Richards’s conversion cutting the
deficit to 15-10.  Marr’s second penalty extended the Oxford lead to eight
points with 20 minutes left. Cambridge worked the ball near the
Oxford touch line with about nine minutes left before turning it
over and Marr clinched the victory with his third penalty in the
final minute.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Bob Bensch  in London at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 